    {
        "content": "<p>The monotone convergence theorem is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MeasureTheory.tendsto_of_lintegral_tendsto_of_monotone#doc\">docs#MeasureTheory.tendsto_of_lintegral_tendsto_of_monotone</a> and there does not seem to have a translation for series in the same way that <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MeasureTheory.hasSum_integral_of_dominated_convergence#doc\">docs#MeasureTheory.hasSum_integral_of_dominated_convergence</a> translates the general theorem for series.</p>",
